		"description": "<p><strong>Age.&nbsp;</strong>Hobgoblins age at a comparable rate to humans.</p>\n<p><strong>Size.&nbsp;</strong>Hobgoblins are frequently over 6 feet tall. Your size is Medium.</p>\n<p><strong>Speed.&nbsp;</strong>You have a base walking speed of 30 feet.</p>\n<p><strong>Darkvision.&nbsp;</strong>You have superior vision in dark and dim conditions. You can see in dim light within 60 feet of you as if it were bright light, and in darkness as if it were dim light. You can&rsquo;t discern color in darkness, only shades of gray.</p>\n<p><strong>Calm Under Pressure.&nbsp;</strong>When you make a saving throw to end an ongoing effect, you can use this trait to automatically succeed. Once you use this trait, you can&rsquo;t use it again until you complete a short or long rest.</p>\n<p><strong>Tactical Brilliance.&nbsp;</strong>You add or subtract your proficiency bonus from your Initiative checks (your choice once you see the results of the initiative rolls for a given combat).</p>",
